name: Definition "Definition EP"
description:
Definition "Definition EP" Definition Music (2002)
Catalogue # DEF001

Definition landed a national distribution deal with their first release, an EP of 8 songs recorded in the college radio studio they used to DJ shows in.

Definition is comprised of emcee Zone (That Dude) and emcee/producer Ill Poetic. "Definition EP" ran out or print in 2005 but officially made it's "re-debut" in 2008.

Available now for the first time in our online store

Tracklisting
1. What is? (f. HuntorPrey)
2. Definition
3. Analysis
4. Amina
5. Reason
6. Reflection
7. To The Beat
8. Wake Up

For more information, please visit www.definitionmusic.net

name: Ill Poetic - "Illumination"
description:
Ill Poetic - "Illumination" Definition Music 
Catalogue # DEF004

The Midwest Regional debut LP from Ill Poetic, "Illumination" was released in Fall 2005. Featuring such prominent artists as Piakhan, Holmskillit, and Zone (That Dude), "Illumination" was the building block that set the stage for Ill Poetic's national debut "The World is Ours".

11. Beyond

13. Yellow

name: Ill Poetic - "The World is Ours"
description:
Ill Poetic - "The World Is Ours" (Dove Ink/Definition Music)
Catalogue # DEF008

"The World is Ours" is Ill Poetic's national debut on the hip-hop scene. Released June 5, 2007, this album recieved glowing reviews and national attention in such places as okayplayer.com and hiphopdx.com, following with national and international tours alongside such hip-hop legends as O.C. and Pharoahe Monche.

The self-produced album is 15 tracks long, featuring appearances from such underground heavyweights as Wordsworth, Blueprint, Illogic and Piakhan.

Tracklisting
 1. Home
 2. Cincilluminati
 3. Common Knowledge (f. Blueprint)
 4. What Yall Want
 5. So Good
 6. Soul Electric
 7. The Beautiful

 9. One More (f. Wordsworth and Zone That Dude)
